<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
The common widespread species of large 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.R.Spence" authorityYear="1996" class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Rosulabryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rosulabryum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Rosulabryum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from central Chile south to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aisén">Aisen</normalizedToken>
. The species is also found in Argentina, the Falkland Islands, Australia, New Zealand and Macquarie Island (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" author="Spence, JR" journalOrPublisher="Telopea" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="99 - 134" refId="B27" refString="Spence, JR, Ramsay, HP, 2019. Revised keys and additions to the Australian Bryaceae (Bryopsida). Telopea 22: 99 - 134, DOI: https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" title="Revised keys and additions to the Australian Bryaceae (Bryopsida)." url="https://doi.org/10.7751/telopea13056" volume="22" year="2019">Spence and Ramsay 2019</bibRefCitation>
). In the Magellanes Region it is largely replaced by 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. perlimbatum" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="perlimbatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. perlimbatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species occurs in a variety of forested and semi-open habitats, often in shade on mesic to damp soil banks, fallen logs, tree stumps and soil-covered ledges. It is characterized by dioicous sexual condition, strongly rosulate stems, large leaves that are irregularly contorted when dry, a costa excurrent into a short awn, a strong limbidium, serrate leaf margins, and brown to red-brown rhizoidal tubers (Illustrations: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" author="Mohamed, MA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bryology" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="401 - 465" refId="B12" refString="Mohamed, MA, 1979. A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species. Journal of Bryology 10 (4): 401 - 465, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" title="A taxonomic study of Bryum billardieri Schwaegr. and related species." url="https://doi.org/10.1179/jbr.1979.10.4.401" volume="10" year="1979">Mohamed 1979</bibRefCitation>
: 407, as 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="Bryum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bryum billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Bryum billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Spence, JR" editor="McCarthy, PM" journalOrPublisher="CSIRO Press, Canberra" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="274 - 348" refId="B26" refString="Spence, JR, Ramsay, HP, 2006. Bryaceae. In: McCarthy, PM, Ed., Flora of Australia, Volume 51, Mosses 1. CSIRO Press, Canberra: 274 - 348" title="Bryaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of Australia, Volume 51, Mosses 1." year="2006">Spence and Ramsay 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 335, as 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fife, AJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" publicationUrl="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" refId="B4" refString="Fife, AJ, 2015. Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N.Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at: https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" title="Flora of New Zealand. Mosses. Fascicle 19, Bryaceae. Lincoln, N. Z., Manaaki Whenua Press (online at:" url="https://www.nzflora.info/publications.htmlmosses" year="2015">Fife 2015</bibRefCitation>
: 84, as 
<taxonomicName class="Bryopsida" family="Bryaceae" genus="R." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="R. billarderii" order="Bryales" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="billarderii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">R. billarderii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
